    "notes": "Finnish has categorical initial (first-syllable) stress. Vowel length (aa ee ii oo uu yy ää öö) marks quantity, not stress. Secondary stress falls on odd-numbered syllables (3rd, 5th…). Source: Karlsson (1999), Finnish: An Essential Grammar; Wikipedia: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Finnish_phonology"
